    slug: "kitab-at-tauhid-english-4-colour-17x24",
    description: `Kitab At-Tauhid (English, 4-Colour, 17x24) is a high-quality English-language edition of one of the most important and influential books in Islamic theology — Kitab At-Tawhid (The Book of Monotheism) by the eminent scholar Shaykh Muhammad ibn Abdul Wahhab (may Allah have mercy on him). This edition is produced in a large 17x24 inch format with distinctive four-colour printing that enhances the visual presentation and readability of the text, making it both a scholarly reference and a beautiful addition to any Islamic library. Kitab At-Tawhid is widely regarded as the foundational text of the Islamic theological movement that emphasises the pure and unadulterated understanding of tawheed (monotheism) based solely upon the Quran and the authentic Sunnah, and this English edition makes this crucial text accessible to English-speaking Muslims, students of Islamic studies, and anyone who wishes to understand the Islamic concept of God in its purest form.

The book is structured as a systematic exposition of the three categories of tawheed that form the foundation of Islamic theology: Tawheed ar-Rububiyyah (the Oneness of Allah's Lordship), Tawheed al-Uluhiyyah (the Oneness of Allah's Worship), and Tawheed al-Asma wa as-Sifat (the Oneness of Allah's Names and Attributes). For each category, the author provides a precise definition, explains its scope and implications, presents the Quranic verses and hadith narrations that establish it, and identifies the specific forms of shirk (polytheism or associating partners with Allah) that violate it. This systematic approach allows the reader to develop a complete and nuanced understanding of what Islam means by tawheed and why it is the single most important concept in the faith.

The section on Tawheed ar-Rububiyyah establishes that Allah alone is the Creator, Sustainer, Provider, Controller, and Planner of all that exists, and that acknowledging this Lordship is the natural and rational conclusion that any thinking person must reach. The author demonstrates how the Quran repeatedly calls upon human beings to reflect upon the signs of Allah's Lordship in creation as evidence of His existence and oneness. The section on Tawheed al-Uluhiyyah — which the author considers the core message of all the prophets — establishes that all acts of worship must be directed exclusively to Allah alone, and that directing any act of worship to anyone or anything other than Allah constitutes shirk, the one sin that Allah has declared He will not forgive. The author identifies numerous forms of shirk that were prevalent in the pre-Islamic world and that continue to exist in various forms in Muslim and non-Muslim societies, including the worship of idols, the veneration of saints and graves, the seeking of intercession from beings other than Allah, the use of talismans and amulets, and the reliance on astrology and fortune-telling. The section on Tawheed al-Asma wa as-Sifat establishes the correct Islamic approach to understanding and affirming Allah's names and attributes, explaining that Allah must be described with the names and attributes that He has described Himself with in the Quran and that the Prophet has described Him with in the authentic hadith, without distortion (tahrif), denial (ta'til), questioning (takytif), or likening Allah to His creation (tamthil).

The four-colour printing of this edition uses distinct colours to highlight different elements of the text, including the Arabic text of the Quranic verses and hadith narrations, the English translation and commentary, the chapter headings and subheadings, and the important points and warnings that the author emphasises. This colour-coded approach makes it easy for readers to navigate the text and to distinguish between the primary sources and the explanatory commentary. The large 17x24 format provides ample space for comfortable reading, clear typography, and generous margins that accommodate personal notes. The binding and paper quality are designed for durability and long-term use. This edition includes a comprehensive introduction that explains the background and significance of Kitab At-Tawhid, a detailed table of contents, and an index of the Quranic verses and hadith narrations cited throughout the book. It is an essential reference for every English-speaking Muslim household, Islamic school library, and student of Islamic theology.`,
