    slug: "loving-our-parents",
    description: `Loving Our Parents is an English-language Islamic book that addresses one of the most important and emphasised topics in the Quran and Sunnah: the rights of parents, the obligation of children to honour, respect, and care for their parents, and the immense spiritual rewards that Islam promises to those who treat their parents with kindness and devotion. The book is written for English-speaking Muslims of all ages, with particular relevance for young adults and married couples who are navigating the often complex dynamics of maintaining strong, loving, and Islamically sound relationships with their parents while managing the demands of their own independent lives. The book draws upon the Quran, the authentic hadith of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), the stories of the righteous predecessors, and the wisdom of classical Islamic scholars to present a comprehensive and practical guide to fulfilling this fundamental religious obligation.

The book opens with a thorough discussion of the Quranic foundation for the obligation of kindness to parents, noting that the command to be kind to parents appears alongside the command to worship Allah alone in multiple Quranic verses, including the famous verse: "And your Lord has decreed that you worship none but Him, and that you be kind to parents. Whether one or both of them attain old age in your life, say not to them a word of contempt, nor repel them, but address them in terms of honour" (Surah Al-Isra 17:23). The author analyses this verse and related passages in detail, explaining the linguistic nuances of the Arabic text that reveal the depth and urgency of the Quranic command. The word "ihsan" (kindness, excellence, beautification) that the Quran uses to describe the required attitude towards parents indicates that mere perfunctory obedience is insufficient; rather, children are required to treat their parents with active, enthusiastic, and beautified kindness that goes beyond the minimum requirements of duty.

The book covers every practical dimension of the parent-child relationship in Islam, including the obligation to speak to parents with respect and gentle language, the prohibition against expressing even the slightest frustration or annoyance at their requests or habits, the duty to provide financial support to parents who are in need, the obligation to care for elderly parents with patience and compassion, the importance of maintaining regular contact and communication with parents even after marriage, the duty to pray for parents both during their lives and after their death, and the special rights of the mother, whom the Prophet (peace be upon him) identified as the person most deserving of one's good company. The book also addresses the Islamic rulings on situations where a parent asks their child to do something that conflicts with Islamic teachings, explaining the principles of "no obedience to creation in disobedience to the Creator" while also emphasising that this disagreement must be expressed with the utmost respect and gentleness.

The book includes a dedicated section on the stories of the prophets and righteous individuals who demonstrated exemplary behaviour towards their parents, including the story of Prophet Ibrahim (peace be upon him) and his father, the story of Prophet Yusuf (peace be upon him) and his parents, and numerous stories from the lives of the companions and the early generations of Muslims. These stories serve as practical illustrations of the principles discussed in the earlier chapters and provide inspiration for readers who wish to improve their own relationships with their parents. The later chapters address the challenges that contemporary Muslims face in maintaining good relationships with their parents, including the demands of work and career, the pressures of married life, cultural differences between generations, the challenge of parents who are not Muslim or who do not practice Islam, and the emotional difficulty of caring for ageing parents. Written in clear, warm, and practical English, this book is an essential guide for every Muslim who wishes to fulfil their duty to their parents and earn the immense rewards that Allah has promised for this act of worship.`,
    metaDescription: "Loving Our Parents is an English Islamic guide to honouring and caring for parents with Quranic verses, hadith, stories, and practical contemporary advice."
